Most of the job ads divide the post into multiple parts: Requirements and description. These two can be linked (e.g. the individual has to collaborate in the team therefore under the requirements section collaboration skills are mentioned), but it is not always the case. In the analysis, the requrirements section is the most important, since the job post mentions that a certain soft skill is required to be able to perform in the job.

In the following example, the "What you will be doing" section mentions collaboration, leadership, and innovation as responsibilities, whereas no soft skill is required in the "What we need from you" section. 
![[Screenshot 2025-08-04 at 17.40.36.png]]


![[Screenshot 2025-08-04 at 17.46.13.png]]

During the analysis, this counts as "no soft skill is required" since the section mentions nothing but hard skills required from the applicant.

